  <div id="text">
    <p>Ye can always pretend to be a bloodthirsty <%= noun1 %>, threatening everyone by waving yer <%= adjective1 %> sword in the air, but until ye learn to <%= verb1 %> like a pirate, ye'll never be <% adverb1 %> accepted as an authentic <%= noun2 %>. So here's what ye do: Cleverly work into yer daily conversations <%= adjective2 %> pirate phrases such as "Ahoy there, <%= pluralNoun1 %>." "Avast, ye <%= pluralNoun2 %>." and "Shiver me <%= pluralNoun3 %>." Remember to drop all yer gs when ye say words such as <em>sailin'</em>, <em>spittin'</em> and <em>fightin'</em>. This will give ye a/an <%= bodyPart1 %> start to being recognized as a swashbucklin' <%= noun3 %>. Once ye have the lingo down pat, it helps to wear a three-cornered <%= noun4 %> on yer head, stash a/an <%= noun5 %> in yer hands, and keep a/an <%= noun6 %> perched atop yer <%= bodyPart2 %>. Aye, now ye be a real pirate!</p>
  </div>
